                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10127: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-18T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 18, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 18—10:21 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>726. As the Japanese Consul General was leaving my office this evening he told me
                    quietly that he was very much worried about safety at Nanking and that perhaps
                    he would be coming to see me in a few days.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department; repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
